When sera were tested for BRSV-IgM without pre-treatment with PGA, calves 1, 2 and 4 showed a transient response (Fig. 1
), with peak S/P% values of 103.5%, 37.4% and 31.2%, respectively, (Table 1
). BRSV-IgM was detectable in calf 1 from 12–16 dpi, and in calf 2 from 9–12 dpi. BRSV-IgM was detectable in calf 4 only on Day 12 post infection. No response was detected in the two control calves.
